Which of the following is true about File I/O in Node applications? both
    (I) Node implements File I/O using simple wrappers around standard POSIX functions. 
    (II) Node File System (fs) module should be imported for File I/O operations.

Which of the following is true about __dirname global object?  ( I )
  (I) The __dirname represents the name of the directory that the currently executing script resides in. 
  (II) The __dirname represents the resolved absolute path of code file.





